<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-03-10T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-03-10T17:00:00-05:00" n="28" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d28">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4/1755: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Acting Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-03-10T17:00:00-05:00">March 10,
                                    1933—5 p.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>298. Your 559, March 9, 1 p.m. and 561, March 9, 8 p.m. I am asking Grew,
                            if he is in a position discreetly to obtain any elucidation of the
                            Japanese stand on the Conference, to telegraph promptly. It might be
                            useful for you to suggest to Simon that he send similar instructions to
                                Lindley.<note n="55" xml:id="d28fn55">Sir Francis Oswald Lindley,
                                British Ambassador to Japan.</note> I agree with you that until the
                            Japanese position is thoroughly clarified we must exert especial
                            caution.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>